cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI

The paper proposes a game-theoretic model for studying influence in networked populations, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SOC). The use of pure-strategy Nash equilibrium as a solution concept suggests that the paper also belongs to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The computational complexity characterizations and algorithms for solving the problem of identifying the most influential individuals suggest that the paper also belongs to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
